      openid connect (oidc) is a simple identity layer on top of the oauth 2.0 protocol. it allows clients to verify the identity of the end-user based on the authentication performed by an authorization server, as well as to obtain basic profile information about the end-user in an interoperable and rest-like manner.
endpoints :
    - get /userinfo
      returns information about the authenticated end-user.
    - get /tokeninfo
      returns information about the used access token.

assistant: user-password.responduser: title : pingfederate
description :
      pingfederate is a cloud-based identity access management (iam) solution that provides secure access to applications and apis.
endpoints :
    - post /oauth2/token
      requests an access token for the authenticated user.
    - post /oauth2/logout
      logs the user out of the application.

assistant: user-password.responduser: title : okta
description :
      okta is an identity management platform for developers. it allows developers to authenticate, authorize, and manage users and their access to cloud applications.
endpoints :
    - post /oauth2/v1/token
      requests an access token for the authenticated user.
    - get /userinfo
      returns information about the authenticated user.

assistant: user-password.responduser: title : auth0
description :
      auth0 is an identity management platform that allows developers to authenticate, authorize, and manage users and their access to applications.
endpoints :
    - post /oauth/token
      requests an access token for the authenticated user.
    - get /userinfo
      returns information about the authenticated user.

assistant: user-password.responduser: title : azure active directory

    - get /me

transferependuser: title : transferwise api
description :
      the transferwise api allows you to integrate with transferwise's platform. transferwise is a global money transfer
      service. this api provides methods to manage users and their profiles, create and manage transfers, and manage
      currencies. the transferwise api uses an api key to authenticate requests.
endpoints :
    - post /users
      create a new user.
    - get /users/{id}
      get a user by id.
    - get /users
      get a list of users.
    - get /users/{id}/profile
      get a user's profile.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}
      get a user's profile field.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history
      get a user's profile field history.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}
      get a user's profile field history from a specific date.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}
      get a user's profile field history between two dates.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}/{interval}
      get a user's profile field history between two dates with a specific interval.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}/interval/{interval}
      get a user's profile field history between two dates with a specific interval.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}/interval/{interval}/summary
      get a user's profile field history between two dates with a specific interval and summary.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}/interval/{interval}/summary/{granularity}
      get a user's profile field history between two dates with a specific interval, summary, and granularity.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}/interval/{interval}/summary/{granularity}/limit/{limit}
      get a user's profile field history between two dates with a specific interval, summary, granularity, and limit.
    - get /users/{id}/profile/{field}/history/{fromdate}/{todate}/interval/{interval}/summary/{granularity}/limit/{limit}/offset/{offset}
      get a user's profile field history between two dates
